Sentencas: Pr 0.2 O 1.9 (PBSC-CPOES) was prepared for the first time through a synergistic approach involving in -situ self -assembly and electrostatic spinning techniques.

Sentencas: PBSC-CPO-ES exhibits exceptionally high oxygen reduction catalytic activity and CO 2 resistance, which is attributed to its unique nanofiber microstructure and abundant presence of heterointerfaces, significantly accelerating the charge transfer process, surface exchange and bulk diffusion of oxygen.

Sentencas: The introduction of CPO not only effectively reduces the thermal expansion of PBSC but also changes the characteristics of oxygen ion transport anisotropy in layered perovskite materials, forming three-dimensional oxygen ion transport pathways.

Sentencas: At 750 degrees C, the single cell employing the PBSC-CPO-ES heterostructure nanofiber attains an impressive peak power density of 1363 mW cm -2 .
Titulo: Synergistically engineered in-situ self-assembled heterostructure composite nanofiber cathode with superior oxygen reduction reaction catalysis for solid oxide fuel cells
